        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "If you're using lazy to handle plugins you can find it here `~/.local/share/nvim/lazy/nvim-lspconfig/lua/lspconfig/server-configurations/clangd.lua` or simply use `find / -type f -iname \"clangd.lua\"` to check where the file exist, then change\r\n```lua\r\nlocal default_capabilities = {\r\n  textDocument = {\r\n    completion = {\r\n      editsNearCursor = true,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n  offsetEncoding =  { 'utrf-8', 'utf-16' } ,\r\n}\r\n```\r\nto\r\n```lua\r\nlocal default_capabilities = {\r\n  textDocument = {\r\n    completion = {\r\n      editsNearCursor = true,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n  offsetEncoding =  'utf-16' ,\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis worked for me.",
